CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, pg. 1, reads: "Fifth Ward Winners - Robert E. (Pappy) Williams, let, and Thomas J. (Tommy) Smith, right, teamed up to win the offices of alderman and constable, respectively, on the Democratic ticket in Fifth Ward with little opposition. Williams was nominated on both tickets, while incumbent Smith was re-elected."
TitMainTitle: Alderman Robert E. "Pappy" Williams wearing light colored coat and gesturing, and Constable Thomas J. "Tommy" Smith wearing striped jacket, standing in interior with light colored block walls, after 1961 election
